.TH AMVERIFY 8
.SH NAME
amverify \- check an Amanda tape for errors
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B amverify
.I config
[
.I slot
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Amverify
reads an Amanda format tape and makes sure each backup image
can be processed by
.B amrestore
and the appropriate system restore program (e.g.\&
.BR tar ).
.LP
.B Amverify
runs
.B amrestore
on each file of the tape and pipes the output
to the system restore program with an option to create a catalogue
of the backup.
The catalogue itself is discarded.
Only the success or failure of the operation itself is of interest.
.LP
If
.I config
is set up to use a tape changer,
.I slot
may be entered to choose a particular tape to process.
Otherwise, slot
.B 0
is the default.
.LP
See the
.IR amanda (8)
man page for more details about Amanda.
.SH AUTHOR
Axel Zinser <fifi@icem.de>
.SH "SEE ALSO"
amrestore(8),
amanda(8)
.SH BUGS
At the moment, only backup tapes created with GNU tar can be verified.
.LP
The
.I slot
parameter is assumed to be numeric.
